-pole distributions of acetylene and ethane are consistent with\nacetylene having a shorter lifetime than ethane that is not sensitive to longer\nadvective timescales, but is augmented by short-term dynamics, such as vertical\nmixing. Conversely, the long lifetime of ethane allows it to be transported to\nhigher latitudes faster than it can be chemically depleted.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 2 Jan 2018 14:05:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-01-03"}
